âWe checked, but not 15 people,â Prawut said, adding that police have not ruled out any group or nationality.
âWe are not focused on the nationality but the individual,â he said, without giving further details.
The main evidence police have for the blast at the Hindu Erawan Shrine popular with Asian tourists is security camera footage.
The footage shows a man with a yellow shirt and dark hair removing a backpack after entering the shrine and walking away from the scene before the explosion.
Twelve of the 20 dead in Mondayâs attack were foreigners, including nationals from China, Hong Kong, Britain, Indonesia, Malaysia and Singapore.
