The most likely perpetrators of the bombing were militant members of a right-wing Turkish organization called the Grey Wolves, a pan-Turkic, extreme right-wing organisation, he said. Davis said their motive may have been revenge for Thailandâs deportation of ethnic Uighurs to China.
âThe Uighur cause is something theyâve latched onto in a big way,â he said, adding that the Grey Wolves were âat the front of the queueâ during an attack on the Thai consulate in Istanbul last month by a mob protesting Thailandâs decision to extradite the Uighurs.
